    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Leaves</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Aqueous extract</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Exhibits low toxicity and affects attachment and penetration of acyclovir-sensitive and acyclovir-resistant HSVs in vitro</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">[
     <xref rid="cit0061" ref-type="bibr">61</xref>,
     <xref rid="cit0062" ref-type="bibr">62</xref>]
    </td>
   </tr>
   <tr>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">28</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">
     <italic>Phyllanthus urinaria</italic>
    </td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Phyllanthus</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Whole plant</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Aqueous extracts</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">Demonstrated the strongest antiviral activities against HSV-1 and HSV-2, with a SI value of more than 33.6</td>
    <td rowspan="1" colspan="1">[
     <xref rid="cit0063" ref-type="bibr">63</xref>]
    </td>
